# DC/DR Drill — Runbook

## Overview

GitOps-based DC/DR switchover and switchback pipeline.
All operations update the deployment repo via git push.
ArgoCD detects the change and reconciles the cluster state.

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `drill.maintenance.yml` | Enable/disable maintenance page (prod + preprod) |
| `drill.scale.yml` | Scale all services DOWN or UP (prod + preprod + nonprod) |
| `drill.mirrormaker2.yml` | Toggle Kafka MirrorMaker2 replication (prod + preprod) |
| `templates/cd/deploy.drill.yml` | Orchestrator — included by deployment repo |

---

## How to Run

### GitLab UI

```
1. Go to: deployment repo → CI/CD → Pipelines → Run pipeline
2. Branch: main
3. Add variable:
     Key:   DRILL_TIER
     Value: prod   OR   preprod   OR   nonprod
4. Click: Run pipeline
5. All relevant manual jobs appear — click in sequence
```

### Switchover Sequence (DC → DR)

```
Stage 1 — maintenance:  Click Maintenance_ON
                        (maintenance page appears on both DC + DR)

Stage 2 — scale:        Click Prod_DC_Scale_All_Down  (scale DC to 0)
                        Click Prod_DR_Scale_All_Up    (scale DR to 1)
                        (traffic now served by DR)

Stage 3 — mirrormaker2: Click Prod_DC_MirrorMaker2_Down  (stop DC replication)
                        Click Prod_DR_MirrorMaker2_Up    (start DR replication)
```

### Switchback Sequence (DR → DC)

```
Stage 2 — scale:        Click Prod_DR_Scale_All_Down  (scale DR to 0)
                        Click Prod_DC_Scale_All_Up    (scale DC to 1)

Stage 3 — mirrormaker2: Click Prod_DR_MirrorMaker2_Down
                        Click Prod_DC_MirrorMaker2_Up

Stage 1 — maintenance:  Click Maintenance_OFF
                        (maintenance page removed)
```

---

## Tier → Jobs Mapping

| DRILL_TIER | Environments Updated | maintenance | scale | mirrormaker2 |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `prod` | prod-dc + prod-dr | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| `preprod` | pre-prod-dc + pre-prod | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| `nonprod` | dev only | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |

---

## Variables Required (GitLab group CI/CD)

| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `GIT_PAT` | GitLab deploy token with push access to deployment repo |
| `DRILL_TIER` | Set at pipeline run time: prod / preprod / nonprod |

---

## Audit Trail

Every drill run produces:
1. **GitLab pipeline record** — who triggered, when, which tier
2. **Git commits in deployment repo** — `drill(prod-dc): replicas=0 [ci skip]`
3. **ArgoCD sync history** — what changed in each cluster

Satisfies PCI-DSS operational change audit requirements.

